<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>My Expense Charts</title>
    <link href="/css/main.css" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <style>
      .chart-container {
        text-align: center;
        margin: 30px 0;
      }
      .chart-title {
        font-size: 24px;
        margin-bottom: 20px;
        color: #fff;
      }
      .chart-image {
        max-width: 100%;
        height: auto;
        border: 8px solid #fff;
        margin: 20px 0;
      }
      .instructions {
        background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
        padding: 20px;
        margin: 20px;
        border-radius: 10px;
        color: #fff;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <h1>ðŸ’° My Expense Analysis</h1>
    
    <div class="instructions">
      <h2>ðŸ“Š How to Generate Your Charts</h2>
      <p>1. Open terminal in VS Code</p>
      <p>2. Run: <code>cd python && python expense_tracker.py</code></p>
      <p>3. Add some expenses and generate charts</p>
      <p>4. Refresh this page to see your results!</p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="chart-container">
      <h2 class="chart-title">Expense Analysis Dashboard</h2>
      <img class="chart-image" src="/charts/expense_analysis.png" 
           alt="Expense Analysis" 
           onerror="this.style.display='none'; document.getElementById('no-chart1').style.display='block';">
      <div id="no-chart1" style="display:none; color: #ccc; font-style: italic;">
        Chart will appear here after running the Python script
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="chart-container">
      <h2 class="chart-title">Expense Statistics</h2>
      <img class="chart-image" src="/charts/expense_stats.png" 
           alt="Expense Statistics"
           onerror="this.style.display='none'; document.getElementById('no-chart2').style.display='block';">
      <div id="no-chart2" style="display:none; color: #ccc; font-style: italic;">
        Chart will appear here after running the Python script
      </div>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>